Biography

JUNIOR (2022-23) – Played in 22 games, averaging 9.9 minutes per game … averaged 2.2 points, 0.3 assists, and 1.5 rebounds per game … saw a career high in minutes against Utah State (Dec. 25) in the Diamond Head Classic … also recorded a career high in field goals made (3) and points (7) against the Aggies … best Conference performance came against USC (Feb. 2) with six points and four rebounds in 20 minutes played (all career high for Pac-12 play).

SOPHOMORE (2021-22) – Medically redshirted the season.

FRESHMAN (2020-21) – Was limited to just seven games due to medical issues ... made his debut Jan.2 against Arizona playing seven minutes ... scored his first collegiate points from the free throw line at UCLA and played 17 minutes.

HIGH SCHOOL – Came to the United States prior to his junior year from the Dominican Republic to play at Veritas Prep in California where he led his team to a 22-12 record as a senior averaging 13.5 points ,4.9 rebounds, and 2.7 assists per game in just his second season ... in just two years at Veritas Prep, he played his way into the top ranks of recruits in the state, ranking No. 14 in California according to 247Sports.com ... throughout his senior season, the lanky wing made a name for himself at elite prep tournaments like the Jerry Tarkanian Classic, earning all-tournament honors, and playing along the top recruits in the country in the Grind Session prep circuit.
